je","Budapest, Budapest, Hungary":"Budapest, Hongarije"},"en":{"about 1220–3 May 1253":"about 1220–3 May 1253","1220–1253":"1220–1253","1205–1241":"1205–1241","1240–1290":"1240–1290","1190–Male":"1190–Deceased","1195–Female":"1195–Deceased","1190":"1190","UM 1219":"about 1219","1205":"1205","1253":"1253","1220":"1220","1241":"1241","1240":"1240","1195":"1195","about 1220":"about 1220","3 May 1253":"3 May 1253","17 March 1241":"17 March 1241","1290":"1290","Mongólia":"Mongolia","Esztergom, Komárom-Esztergom, Hungary":"Esztergom, Komárom-Esztergom, Hungary","Poland":"Poland","Pest, Budapest, Pest-Pilis-Solt-Kiskun, Ungheria":"Pest, Budapest, Pest-Pilis-Solt-Kiskun, Hungary","Budapest, Budapest, Hungary":"Budapest, Hungary","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Agnez","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized version of the Greek name <i>Hagnē</i>, from the feminine form of the adjective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1354912,"age":21,"year":"1241","julianDay":2174327,"description":"The Mongolian Tatars devastated the country. Their presence, which lasted a year, halted development for at least a century. After the warfare with the Hungarians, the Tatars did not continue towards the west.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Agnez Riurikova de Halich was born about 1220, in Mongolia, her father, Mustilau de Halich, was 32 and her mother, da Kumânia, was 26. She married Хан Котен in 1240, in Poland. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died on 3 May 1253, in Budapest, Hungary, at the age of 34."},"et":{"about 1220–3 May 1253":"umbes 1220–3. mai 1253","1220–1253":"1220–1253","1205–1241":"1205–1241","1240–1290":"1240–1290","1190–Male":"1190–Surnud","1195–Female":"1195–Surnud","1190":"1190","UM 1219":"umbes 1219","1205":"1205","1253":"1253","1220":"1220","1241":"1241","1240":"1240","1195":"1195","about 1220":"umbes 1220","3 May 1253":"3. mai 1253","17 March 1241":"17. märts 1241","1290":"1290","Mongólia":"Mongoolia","Esztergom, Komárom-Esztergom, Hungary":"Esztergom, Komárom-Esztergom, Ungari","Poland":"Poola","Pest, Budapest, Pest-Pilis-Solt-Kiskun, Ungheria":"Pest, Budapest, Pest-Pilis-Solt-Kiskun, Ungari","Budapest, Budapest, Hungary":"Budapest, Ungari"},"fi":{"about 1220–3 May 1253":"noin 1220–3. toukokuuta 1253","1220–1253":"1220–1253","1205–1241":"1205–1241","1240–1290":"1240–1290","1190–Male":"1190–Kuollut","1195–Female":"1195–Kuollut","1190":"1190","UM 1219":"noin 1219","1205":"1205","1253":"1253","1220":"1220","1241":"1241","1240":"1240","1195":"1195","about 1220":"noin 1220","3 May 1253":"3. toukokuuta 1253","17 March 1241":"17. maaliskuuta 1241","1290":"1290","Mongólia":"Mongolia","Esztergom, Komárom-Esztergom, Hungary":"Esztergom, Komárom-Esztergom, Unkari","Poland":"Puola","Pest, Budapest, Pest-Pilis-Solt-Kiskun, Ungheria":"Pest, Budapest, Pest-Pilis-Solt-Kiskun, Unkari","Budapest, Budapest, Hungary":"Budapest, Unkari"},"fr":{"about 1220–3 May 1253":"environ 1220–3 mai 1253","1220–1253":"1220–1253","1205–1241":"1205–1241","1240–1290":"1240–1290","1190–Male":"1190–Décédé","1195–Female":"1195–Décédée","1190":"1190","UM 1219":"environ 1219","1205":"1205","1253":"1253","1220":"1220","1241":"1241","1240":"1240","1195":"1195","about 1220":"environ 1220","3 May 1253":"3 mai 1253","17 March 1241":"17 mars 1241",